Perfect ğŸ’¯ â€” having a **ready Jenkinsfile** makes a big impression in interviews because it shows youâ€™ve actually done hands-on work. Hereâ€™s a **mini end-to-end CI/CD pipeline** with all the stages:

---

# ğŸ”¹ **Sample Jenkinsfile for CI/CD**

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    environment {
        REGISTRY = "dockerhub_username/myapp"
        IMAGE_TAG = "build-${BUILD_NUMBER}"
        KUBE_CONFIG = credentials('kubeconfig-cred')  // stored in Jenkins
    }

    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git branch: 'develop', url: 'https://github.com/org/myapp.git'
            }
        }

        stage('Build & Test') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm install'
                sh 'npm test'
            }
        }

        stage('Code Quality') {
            steps {
                withSonarQubeEnv('SonarQubeServer') {
                    sh 'sonar-scanner'
                }
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                sh "docker build -t $REGISTRY:$IMAGE_TAG ."
            }
        }

        stage('Push Docker Image') {
            steps {
                withCredentials([usernamePassword(credentialsId: 'dockerhub-cred',
                                                  usernameVariable: 'USER',
                                                  passwordVariable: 'PASS')]) {
                    sh "echo $PASS | docker login -u $USER --password-stdin"
                    sh "docker push $REGISTRY:$IMAGE_TAG"
                }
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy to Kubernetes') {
            steps {
                sh """
                helm upgrade --install myapp ./helm/myapp \
                  --set image.repository=$REGISTRY \
                  --set image.tag=$IMAGE_TAG \
                  --kubeconfig $KUBE_CONFIG
                """
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        success {
            echo "âœ… Build #${BUILD_NUMBER} succeeded and deployed with image $IMAGE_TAG"
        }
        failure {
            echo "âŒ Build #${BUILD_NUMBER} failed. Check logs."
        }
    }
}
```

---

# ğŸ”¹ **Pipeline Flow**

1. **Checkout** â†’ Pull code from GitHub.
2. **Build & Test** â†’ Install dependencies, run unit tests.
3. **Code Quality** â†’ SonarQube scan.
4. **Build Docker Image** â†’ Package app into Docker image.
5. **Push Docker Image** â†’ Push to DockerHub/ECR.
6. **Deploy to Kubernetes** â†’ Helm upgrades deployment with new image.

---

